               <msContents>
                  <summary>Copy of a petition of Aurelius Isidoros against Kastor, Ammonianos and their heirs, the culmination of a long struggle: Isidoros tries to recover the wheat and beans that they borrowed or the 3 oxen given as security; the praeses' reply follows, promising to provide assistance; the text is preceded by the covering letter to the praepositus</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; the back is blank</note>
                     <note type="general">24 lines of writing with 2 more by a second hand: the main hand is minute and practiced</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
